te increased commitment to the study of international relations in a context that would enable students to understand the importance of developing practical policies within a theoretical and analytical framework previous wesson lecturers have included such distinguished speakers as mcgeorge bundy willi declerq condoleezza rice mikhail gorbachev fernando henrique cardoso and mary robinson display events from month or quarter winter spring summer fall all months 1 january 2 february 3 march 4 april 5 may 6 june 7 july 8 august 9 september 10 october 11 november 12 december year 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 2004 2003 2002 2001 2000 1999 1998 1997 mar 5 2008 2008 robert g wesson lecture economic growth poverty and democracy in latin america a president's perspective cddrl fsi stanford lecture the honorable vicente fox former president of mexico video+ audio+ audio & video transcripts available mar 13 2007 2007 robert g wesson lecture caesarism in democratic politics reflections on max weber lecture gerhard casper president emeritus of stanford university peter and helen bing professor in undergraduate education at stanford professor of law professor of political science by courtesy fsi senior fellow forum on contemporary europe research affiliate pdf+ paper available nov 16 2005 taming american power the global response to us primacy lecture stephen walt academic dean robert and renee belfer professor of international affairs harvard university's john f kennedy school of government feb 27 2002 problematic relationship between sovereignty and humanitarian intervention lecture the honorable gareth evans president international crisis group brussels jan 16 2001 democracy and social justice democracy and human rights lecture amartya sen nobel laureate professor trinity college cambridge united kingdom january 2001 events search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages select events from marc